  • Constructor Details

    • Order

      public Order​(Unit unit, Asset asset, int qty, int price, java.lang.Boolean isBuy)
      This constructor sets the trade ID of the order and adds the trade specific information to the object.
      Parameters:
      unit - Unit of the user that placed the trade
      asset - Asset that is being traded
      qty - Amount of the asset that is being traded
      price - Price at which the asset is being traded
      isBuy - Used to track the order type, True for Buy orders, False for Sell orders

    • Order

      public Order​(Unit unit, Asset asset, int qty, int price, java.lang.Boolean isBuy, int ID)
      The constructor used to create an order from a database object.
      Parameters:
      unit - Unit that the order was placed on behalf of
      asset - The asset that is being traded
      qty - The quantity of the assest that is beingtraded
      price - The price at which the asset is being traded at
      isBuy - The type of order, true for Buy orders, false for sell orders
      ID - The ID of the order from the database.
